= 1. (1.54)
This is the equation of an ellipse with semi-axes equal to |σp1| and |σp2|, respectively, proving the stated claim. As the orientation of the face changes, the tip of the stress vector sweeps around Lame ́’s ellipse. Note that while the shape of the ellipse is not affected by the sign of the principal stresses, the orientation of the stress vector does depend on their sign. For instance, the stress vector τ n shown in fig. 1.17 corresponds to σp1 > 0 and


