(1.69)
Finally, these results can be combined in eq. (1.67) to yield the rather cumbersome expression γ23 = arcsin N/D. With the help of the small displacement assumption, see eq. (1.61), the numerator simplifies to N ≈ 2(∂u2/∂x3 + ∂u3/∂x2) dx2dx3, whereas the denominator reduces to D ≈ 2(1+ ∂u2/∂x2 + ∂u3/∂x3) dx2dx3. With these simplifications, the shearing strain component becomes
γ23 ≈ ∂u2/∂x3 + ∂u3/∂x2
