Consider a sheet of material of length L, width b, and thickness t, subjected to a tension load P , as depicted in the left portion of fig. 2.11. Assuming the stress distribution to be uniform over the sheet’s cross-section, the total load the material can carry is Pmax = σultbt, where σult is the ultimate allowable stress for the material.
